-- int_deduped_customer_channels.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate layer: deduplicate multiple channel attributions per customer
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_customer_revenue_by_channel.sql
```sql
-- Mart layer: customer revenue aggregated by attribution channel and store city
WITH transactions AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.store_id,
        t.amount,
        COALESCE(cc.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
        COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_customer_channels') }} cc
        ON cc.customer_id = t.customer_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
        ON s.store_id = t.store_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM transactions
GROUP BY
    channel,
    city
ORDER BY
    channel,
    city
